                <h2 id="what-are-cookies">1. What Are Cookies?</h2>
                <p>
                    Cookies are small text files that are placed on your device (computer, smartphone, tablet) when you visit a website. They are widely used to make websites work efficiently, remember your preferences, and provide information to website owners about how visitors use their sites.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Cookies typically contain two pieces of information: a unique identifier and some site-specific data. They are stored locally on your device and are sent back to the website on each subsequent visit, allowing the site to recognize you and remember your preferences.
                </p>

                <h3>Types of Technologies We Use</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Cookies:</strong> Small text files stored on your device</li>
                    <li><strong>Local Storage:</strong> Browser storage for larger amounts of data that persists across sessions</li>
                    <li><strong>Session Storage:</strong> Temporary storage that is cleared when you close your browser</li>
                    <li><strong>Web Beacons:</strong> Tiny graphics used to track page views and user actions</li>
                </ul>

                <h2 id="how-we-use">2. How We Use Cookies</h2>
                <p>Clear Window uses cookies and similar technologies for several important purposes:</p>

                <h3>Essential Functionality</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> Keeping you logged in securely as you navigate the platform</li>
                    <li><strong>Security:</strong> Protecting against fraudulent activity and maintaining platform integrity</li>
                    <li><strong>Session Management:</strong> Maintaining your session state and form data</li>
                    <li><strong>Anti-Brigading:</strong> Detecting and preventing coordinated manipulation attempts</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>User Preferences</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Theme Selection:</strong> Remembering if you prefer dark mode or light mode</li>
                    <li><strong>Language Settings:</strong> Storing your language preference</li>
                    <li><strong>Accessibility Options:</strong> Maintaining your accessibility settings</li>
                    <li><strong>Cookie Consent:</strong> Remembering your cookie preferences</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Performance and Analytics</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Usage Patterns:</strong> Understanding how users interact with Clear Window</li>
                    <li><strong>Feature Optimization:</strong> Identifying which features are most valuable</li>
                    <li><strong>Error Tracking:</strong> Detecting and diagnosing technical issues</li>
                    <li><strong>Performance Monitoring:</strong> Measuring page load times and responsiveness</li>
                </ul>

                <h2 id="types-of-cookies">3. Types of Cookies We Use</h2>

                <h3>
                    <span class="cookie-type cookie-essential">Essential</span>
                    Strictly Necessary Cookies
                </h3>
                <p>
                    These cookies are essential for the platform to function properly. Without these cookies, services you have requested (like submitting reviews or logging in) cannot be provided. These cookies cannot be disabled through our cookie management system, but you can block them in your browser settings (though this may break site functionality).
                </p>
                <p><strong>Examples:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Session authentication cookies</li>
                    <li>Security tokens for CSRF protection</li>
                    <li>Load balancing cookies</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>
                    <span class="cookie-type cookie-functional">Functional</span>
                    Functional Cookies
                </h3>
                <p>
                    These cookies enable enhanced functionality and personalization. They may be set by us or by third-party providers whose services we have added to our pages. If you do not allow these cookies, some or all of these services may not function properly.
                </p>
                <p><strong>Examples:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Theme preference (dark/light mode)</li>
                    <li>Language settings</li>
                    <li>Regional preferences</li>
                    <li>Accessibility settings</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>
