                <h2 id="control-cookies">6. How to Control Cookies</h2>

                <h3>Cookie Consent Banner</h3>
                <p>
                    When you first visit Clear Window, you'll see a cookie consent banner that allows you to:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Accept All:</strong> Allow all cookies for the best experience</li>
                    <li><strong>Reject Optional:</strong> Only allow essential cookies required for core functionality</li>
                    <li><strong>Customize:</strong> Choose which types of cookies you want to allow</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    You can change your cookie preferences at any time by clicking the "Cookie Settings" link in the footer or by clearing your cookies and revisiting the site.
                </p>

                <h3>Browser Cookie Controls</h3>
                <p>
                    Most web browsers allow you to control cookies through their settings. You can typically:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>View cookies stored by websites you visit</li>
                    <li>Delete individual cookies or all cookies</li>
                    <li>Block all cookies from being set</li>
                    <li>Block only third-party cookies</li>
                    <li>Set cookies to be deleted when you close your browser</li>
                    <li>Create exceptions for specific websites</li>
                </ul>

                <h2 id="browser-settings">7. Browser-Specific Settings</h2>

                <h3>Google Chrome</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Click the three-dot menu icon → Settings</li>
                    <li>Navigate to Privacy and security → Cookies and other site data</li>
                    <li>Choose your cookie settings or click "See all cookies and site data" to manage individual cookies</li>
                    <li>Optional: Enable "Clear cookies and site data when you quit Chrome"</li>
                </ol>

                <h3>Mozilla Firefox</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Click the menu button → Settings</li>
                    <li>Select Privacy & Security</li>
                    <li>Under "Cookies and Site Data," choose your preferences</li>
                    <li>Click "Manage Data" to view and delete specific cookies</li>
                </ol>

                <h3>Safari (macOS)</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Click Safari → Preferences</li>
                    <li>Select the Privacy tab</li>
                    <li>Choose your cookie blocking preferences</li>
                    <li>Click "Manage Website Data" to view and remove specific cookies</li>
                </ol>

                <h3>Microsoft Edge</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Click the three-dot menu → Settings</li>
                    <li>Navigate to Cookies and site permissions → Manage and delete cookies and site data</li>
                    <li>Choose your cookie preferences or manage specific sites</li>
                </ol>

                <h3>Safari (iOS)</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Open Settings app</li>
                    <li>Scroll down and tap Safari</li>
                    <li>Under Privacy & Security, adjust cookie settings</li>
                    <li>Tap "Advanced" → "Website Data" to manage stored data</li>
                </ol>

                <h3>Chrome (Android)</h3>
                <ol>
                    <li>Open Chrome app</li>
                    <li>Tap the three-dot menu → Settings</li>
                    <li>Tap Site settings → Cookies</li>
                    <li>Toggle cookies on or off, or manage exceptions</li>
                </ol>

